Description: AIMS OS — GNOME desktop, installer and core user applications (slim)
 The slim AIMS OS user-facing layer. Installs the GNOME desktop
 (task-gnome-desktop — shell, GDM, Files, Web, Terminal — without the
 gnome metapackage's games and bloat), the Calamares graphical
 installer plus its Debian settings, the Plymouth boot splash
 framework (themed by aims-os-branding), Firefox ESR with the French
 locale, LibreOffice with the French dictionary and thesaurus, the
 standard fonts pack, basic document / image / media viewers, the
 free GStreamer codec stack, Flatpak with the GNOME Software plugin
 (Flathub remote registered by an AIMS-specific first-boot service),
 the NetworkManager stack with OpenVPN support, and a baseline set of
 utilities (KeepassXC, zsh, fastfetch, ripgrep, fzf, bat, p7zip,
 screenshots, neovim, httpie, pandoc, pdftk-java, yt-dlp, redis-server).
 .
 Heavier / optional pieces live in companion metapackages so the live
 ISO stays small and students can pick what they need on first boot:
 .
   * aims-os-desktop-extras  Chromium, GIMP, Inkscape, Shotwell,
                             Evolution, ghostwriter, fish, tilix,
                             flameshot, English LibreOffice helpers
                             and dictionaries, non-free codecs.
   * aims-os-desktop-dev     OpenJDK 21, Gradle, Kotlin, PHP, Composer,
                             adb/fastboot, Docker, Podman, kubectl,
                             Ansible, rustup. The full Web/Android
                             Development + MLOps + Containers stack
                             from v2.0; ~2 GB on disk.
   * aims-os-everything      Pulls every AIMS OS metapackage at once,
                             for users who want the v2.0 "complete"
                             experience in one apt install.
 .
 Node.js 22 LTS, Bun, Deno, uv, Cursor and VSCodium continue to be
 installed via chroot hooks (Node from NodeSource, the rest from
 upstream binary releases) since the Trixie packages are EOL or
 absent.
 .
 The fr_FR.UTF-8 locale and Africa/Dakar timezone are configured at
 the system level by aims-os-core; aims-os-centre-senegal layers the
 Senegal-specific bookmarks, content and intranet wiring on top.
